snippet.title: Deadpool & Wolverine RECAP: Complete Marvel History (1998-2024)
snippet.description:
Here’s EVERYTHING You Need To Know Before Deadpool & Wolverine! Let our sponsor BetterHelp connect you to a therapist who can support you - all from the comfort of your own home. Visit https://betterhelp.com/newrockstars and enjoy a special discount on your first month.

If you have any questions about the brand relating to how the therapists are licensed, their privacy policy, or therapist compensation model, check out this FAQ: https://www.betterhelp.com/your-questions-answered/

Since 1998, there have been over 80 Marvel movies and shows, and ALL OF THEM could come back as references in Deadpool & Wolverine. The MCU, the Fox X-Men franchise, the Blade trilogy, the Sam Raimi Spider-Man trilogy, the Fantastic Four films, the Daredevil films, the Netflix Marvel series, Agents of SHIELD… it’s all too much to catch up on, so which of them do we NEED to rewatch and know about before watching Deadpool & Wolverine? Erik Voss gives a complete recap / primer / explanation of the full history of Marvel in film, from the early days of Blade in 1998 and Kevin Feige meeting Hugh Jackman while working on X-Men (2000). Included at the end of this recap: a CHEAT SHEET of the THREE MOVIES you must make time to rewatch before going into Deadpool & Wolverine (2024).

Check out our sweet, sweet merch! http://www.NerdRiot.shop

snippet.title: Trying To Eat 16 Cheeseburgers To Beat The Record at Jack Brown's
snippet.description:
Trying to eat 16 cheeseburgers to beat the Burger Eating Record Challenge at Jack Brown's in Nashville, Tennessee!! Each year, hungry diners have a chance to eat as many burgers as possible! Beat the current record to win burgers for free, a groovy t-shirt, and a spot up on the wall of fame! Losers must pay the full price of every burger ordered! I was up against @willmorseeats who conquered 15 burgers this year! 

[The all time record of 21 burgers at the Germantown restaurant is held by @gordonhazzard]
***
FOLLOW ME ON TWITCH: https://www.twitch.tv/katinaeatskilos
STACK UP FOR MILITARY VETERANS: https://stackup.org/
FOLLOW ME ON FACEBOOK: https://www.facebook.com/katinaeatskilos/
FOLLOW ME ON IG: https://www.instagram.com/katinaeatskilos/
WEBSITE: https://www.katinaeatskilos.com
***
About Me:
I'm a 5'2 former women's physique bodybuilder on a mission to sample delicious foods from around the world! I tackle restaurant challenges, sample new food menus, and explore the unique eats in various cities. To balance out the calorie intake of weekly food challenges, I continue to pursue my love of fitness through extreme athletic adventures such as ultra-running and biking. I hope you'll join me at my table!

snippet.title: Kentucky's Undefeated 8lb+ Torta Challenge!!
snippet.description:
Taking on La Torta Loco's undefeated 8lb+ El Nono Torta Challenge in Crescent Springs, Kentucky! This massive torta is stuffed with 1lb each of grilled chicken, fried chicken, carne asada, hot dogs, and chorizo. In addition, there is an entire potato, 8 slices of ham, 3 eggs, and large heap of veggies. Very hungry and brave diners have just 45 minutes to finish the entire sandwich in order to earn their $49.99 meal for free, a groovy t-shirt OR lucha libre mask, and a spot up on the wall of fame!

snippet.title: THE BEST FOOD CHALLENGE I'VE EVER ATTEMPTED | KENDALL'S CHICKEN FRY | OKLAHOMA EP.2 | BeardMeatsFood
snippet.description:
Today I'm full of beans, because we're attempting a food challenge which has been on my bucket list for years now...

We're at Kendall's in Noble, Oklahoma having a crack at their infamous, twenty year old, 'Chicken Fry Challenge'!

This thing costs $50 and consists of three huge chicken fried steaks, a double serving of mashed potatoes, double serving of green beans, a biscuit, side salad and two of their renowned cinnamon rolls. Finish inside one hour and it's yours on the house, plus you get a choice of winner's garment (they have a selection of long/short sleeved tops with a bunch of different designs on them). 

***NEW VIDEOS EVERY THURSDAY AND SUNDAY AT 7PM UK TIME***

FOLLOW ME: Facebook/Twitter/Instagram: @BeardMeatsFood

FOLLOW MRS BEARD: Instagram: @Mrs_Beard_Eats

MY PODCAST:

@BreakingBreadPD - A good old fashioned chin wag with my co-host Josh Gudgeon, in a studio so plush it makes it look like we know what we're doing.

MERCHANDISE - DISTRIBUTED BY TEESPRING: 

Use the merchandise shelf above or the following link - https://teespring.com/en-GB/stores/beard-meats-food-store

snippet.title: BROKEN YOLK'S INFAMOUS 'IRON MAN' CHALLENGE | TEXAS EP.1 | BeardMeatsFood
snippet.description:
Today I'm eating breakfast in Texas! In the first instalment from this expedition I'm at Broken Yolk Cafe in Spring, TX taking on their infamous IRON MAN CHALLENGE!

Competitors get one hour to consume a 12 egg omelette topped with cheese, chilli, onions and mushrooms, accompanied by a huge mountain of home fries and some biscuits. Sink it in the allotted time and not only is the $35 meal free, but you get a winner's t-shirt and a wooden plaque to be displayed in the restaurant for eternity!

***NEW VIDEOS EVERY THURSDAY AND SUNDAY AT 7PM UK TIME***

FOLLOW ME: Facebook/Twitter/Instagram: @BeardMeatsFood

FOLLOW MRS BEARD: Instagram: @Mrs_Beard_Eats

MY PODCAST:

@BreakingBreadPD - A good old fashioned chin wag with my co-host Josh Gudgeon, in a studio that looks so plush it makes it look like we know what we're doing.

MERCHANDISE (DISTRIBUTED BY TEESPRING): 

Use the merchandise shelf above or the following link - https://teespring.com/en-GB/stores/beard-meats-food-store

ANSWERS TO COMMON QUESTIONS & ADDITIONAL INFO:

Q: How come you don’t get fat? 
A: I eat like this for 1 hour of a 168 hour long week. In simple terms, I eat at caloric maintenance over the course of time, meaning I don’t gain weight. If you're interested in learning more, see the ‘But How Come You're Not Fat' and 'It Was Just A Normal Day...' videos available on my channel.

Q: Don’t you worry about your health?
A: Not in particular. I’m active. I eat nutrient dense foods five days a week. And, I get quarterly bloods done, amongst other health checks.

BIOGRAPHY, COMMON QUESTION’S AND TRIVIA:

See IMDB profile - https://www.imdb.com/name/nm8467462/bio

snippet.title: MAX AND LOUIE'S ALL AMERICAN BREAKFAST STACK CHALLENGE | TEXAS EP.7 | BeardMeatsFood
snippet.description:
In the seventh instalment of the Texas trip, I'm paying a visit to Max & Louie's New York Diner in San Antonio to take on their 'Robert Stack Challenge', which it turns out is named after the American character actor and sportsman of the same name...yeah I know, I've never heard of him either...

Participants get 25 minutes in which to eat a stack of pancakes, waffles, french toast, bacon, eggs, sausage, chicken and somewhat bizarrely...a slice of orange...in order to win the meal free, a swanky tee and even a mug, provided you can box off a dessert too!

***NEW VIDEOS EVERY THURSDAY AND SUNDAY AT 7PM UK TIME***

FOLLOW ME: Facebook/Twitter/Instagram: @BeardMeatsFood

FOLLOW MRS BEARD: Instagram: @Mrs_Beard_Eats

MY PODCAST:

@BreakingBreadPD - A good old fashioned chin wag with my co-host Josh Gudgeon, in a studio that looks so plush it makes it look like we know what we're doing.

MERCHANDISE (DISTRIBUTED BY TEESPRING): 

Use the merchandise shelf above or the following link - https://teespring.com/en-GB/stores/beard-meats-food-store

ANSWERS TO COMMON QUESTIONS & ADDITIONAL INFO:

Q: How come you don’t get fat? 
A: I eat like this for 1 hour of a 168 hour long week. In simple terms, I eat at caloric maintenance over the course of time, meaning I don’t gain weight. If you're interested in learning more, see the ‘But How Come You're Not Fat' and 'It Was Just A Normal Day...' videos available on my channel.

Q: Don’t you worry about your health?
A: Not in particular. I’m active. I eat nutrient dense foods five days a week. And, I get quarterly bloods done, amongst other health checks.

snippet.title: THE UNDEFEATED GRAND CHAMPION BBQ CHALLENGE | The Trip To Bristol Pt.2
snippet.description:
They say it's impossible. We'll see about that...

Today I'm in Bristol taking on Bare Grills' undefeated BBQ challenge. It would probably be easier to itemise what isn't on this thing, rather than what is; but it's essentially a ton of BBQ favourites...Brisket, ribs, wings, hot links, burnt ends, pulled pork, two different types of loaded fries, onion rings, corn, bread rolls and...as if that weren't enough...a huge burger too!

£45 minutes to order, but if you can take it down inside 60 minutes it's yours for FREE!

snippet.title: THE UNDEFEATED CODBUSTER GIANT FISH & CHIP CHALLENGE | C.O.B. Ep.171
snippet.description:
Fish & Chips...Some say the pinnacle of British cuisine...I'm not sure I'd agree, but one thing I do know is that we can't have an undefeated chippy platter challenge just sat there can we? Today's mission...Give it a heavy battering!

£18 is the cost to partake in Misterton Chippy & Bistro's 'Cod Buster' challenge. 32oz of fish, battered, accompanied by nigh on 4lb of chips, gravy, curry sauce, mushy peas, beans and two slices of buttered bread. Down it all inside 40 minutes and it's yours on the house. And so too is a coveted winners t-shirt!

snippet.title: Moving to New York City in 2024? What to ACTUALLY expect.
snippet.description:
Moving to a new city is a huge life change. If you're an average person wanting to move to New York City in 2024, this video is full of things you should know about the city before you arrive... from the current state of the city to my advice on what it's really like. I am a transplant who has lived in NYC for the last 7 years and have had a ton of experiences here both with roommates and living alone so hopefully you can trust me ;) I'm hoping me sharing these tips can help just one other person in their journey.

Here are all the sources I referenced in my video:

*SAFETY/CRIME*
https://www.nyc.gov/site/nypd/news/p00099/nypd-january-2024-citywide-crime-statistics
@TheRenderQ's video referenced at 2:51 (watch his full video for all the info on amazon lockers!): https://youtu.be/GuE_P4IfPio?si=smIKgSwtqsOiTat2

*COVID IN THE CITY*
https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/10/upshot/covid-pandemic-wave.html
https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2024/02/13/covid-isolation-guidelines-cdc-change/

*APARTMENTS & RENTING*
My moving series: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLuR-6QF6WOR0YYYGIqt-wPf34DeRs3iS4&si=rHyUHXafT-mb0eVu
NYC Housing Connect: https://housingconnect.nyc.gov/PublicWeb/search-lotteries
https://gothamist.com/news/want-an-nyc-apartment-under-2400-good-luck-with-that
https://streeteasy.com/blog/2024-housing-market-predictions/
https://inhabit.corcoran.com/nyc-residential-rental-market-report-jan-2024/#:~:text=January%20is%20historically%20a%20strong,be%20tenants%20into%20the%20marketplace.

*VOLUNTEERING*
https://www.newyorkcares.org/home?gad_source=1
https://www.bowery.org/
https://www.cityharvest.org/

*PUBLIC LIBRARY*
Apply for a library card online here: https://www.nypl.org/library-card/new
https://www.nypl.org/about/service-impacts
https://gothamist.com/news/libraries-summer-school-police-and-composting-face-cuts-amid-nyc-budget-crisis
https://council.nyc.gov/carlina-rivera/2024/02/12/ny-daily-news-nyc-library-use-surged-before-adams-budget-cuts-eliminated-sunday-service/

*VOTING*
https://www.nycvotes.org/
https://elections.ny.gov/registration-and-voting-deadlines

*NYC SUBWAYS*
https://nypost.com/2024/01/22/metro/ugly-mta-subway-safety-rails-at-nyc-station-dont-impress-straphangers-whats-the-point/
https://www.thecity.nyc/2023/02/03/mta-debuts-open-gangway-trains/
https://www.nytimes.com/2024/01/30/nyregion/subway-mta-fare-gates.html

*CONGESTION PRICING PROGRAM*
https://portal.311.nyc.gov/article/?kanumber=KA-03612
https://new.mta.info/project/CBDTP
https://council.nyc.gov/joseph-borelli/2023/02/27/nyc-congestion-pricing-pushed-back-to-2024-costing-250m-in-revenue-mta-says/

*INFRASTRUCTURE*
https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2024/02/13/climate/flooding-sea-levels-groundwater.html
https://climate.nasa.gov/news/3285/nasa-led-study-pinpoints-areas-of-new-york-city-sinking-rising/#:~:text=New%20York%20City%2C%20which%20sits,is%20now%20sinking%20back%20down.&text=The%20scientists%20found%20that%20on,toenail%20grows%20in%20a%20month.

Moving to NYC in 2021 video: https://youtu.be/RqNNVpJgey8?si=M8OKkD_-vKdati4F
Moving to NYC in 2022 video: https://youtu.be/-9D212fLZZI?si=nqsMqGQ7uML-iDEB
Moving to NYC in 2023 video: https://youtu.be/Cibof3UtgK8?si=CXP_Z2fW8IzwMvpW

Beijinos e abraços,
Carissa, Iwan, Frankie & Albi

Our Story:
We are Carissa, Iwan & Frankie the sausage dog, and in 2020 decided one night over a bottle of wine that moving from North Wales to Portugal would be a good idea. Within a month we were on the road to Portugal to find the perfect piece of land to call home. We picked up Albi, Joao and Simao the cats along the way, as well as Diogo the podengo and a flock of chickens.

Subscribe to follow our project as we turn an old stone barn into our home, and learn the ropes of looking after a piece of land to make an abundant garden and one day, our very own winery.

snippet.description:

Get up to 60% OFF your subscription ➡Here: https://go.babbel.com/t?bsc=usa-influ-eg-dt-1m&btp=default&utm_term=generic_v1&utm_medium=paidsocial&utm_source=YouTube&utm_campaign=americanviscountess&utm_content=Influencer..Jul-2024..USA-TATAM..1200m60-yt-americanviscountess-jul-2024

🇮🇹🏡✨ Check out my brand NEW https://www.youtube.com/@julieinitaly YouTube Channel - Authentic Italy Delivered to your Doorstep! I'll be bringing you flea market finds, rare antiques, vintage fashions, and of course, some Little Italian House renovations. Subscribe here: https://www.youtube.com/@julieinitaly 🛍️🖼️👗🔨

ROUND-BREAKING AI BRINGS HISTORY TO LIFE – NEW EXHIBITION UNVEILS THE UNTOLD STORY OF A GILDED AGE AMERICAN HEIRESS.  
 
A new exhibition offers a glimpse into the captivating world of Alberta Sturges Montagu, the 9th Countess of Sandwich, and an American Heiress from the renowned era known as The Gilded Age. 

Curated by Mapperton’s very own American Viscountess, Julie Montagu, the "American Heiress" collection is comprised of more than 10,000 previously unseen letters exchanged between Alberta (Sturges) Montagu and her family, as well as the peerage at large. 

Dating from 1888 to 1951, these letters constitute the largest unpublished private collection of correspondence from the period. They offer a remarkable glimpse into the life of a "dollar bride" during the Gilded Age, shedding light on both triumphs and struggles.
 
The exhibition takes innovation to the next level by introducing Alberta AI, a ground-breaking creation that brings her story to life like never before. 

“With the aid of cutting-edge AI technology, we've resurrected Alberta's voice, allowing her to answer visitors’ burning questions about her remarkable journey,” says Julie Montagu, Viscountess Hinchingbrooke.

🌟 Support the creation of "American Viscountess" and help us produce more extraordinary historic house episodes by becoming a Patron at https://www.patreon.com/americanviscountess! 

Here, you'll enjoy early and ad-free access to all our vlogs and Historic House episodes, along with exclusive behind-the-scenes videos, American Viscountess merchandise, and more! Your support is what fuels these vital Historic House episodes. 🎥

snippet.title: Stepping Back from Social Media Made Me Richer In Life
snippet.description:
In this video, I share what happened when I lessened my time on social media and how it will transform my life for the better. By stepping back from the time sucking scrolling and constant filming, I was able to focus on what truly matters, leading to a wealth of fulfillment and happiness. Join me as I discuss the benefits of disconnecting from social media and the positive impact it had on my well-being. If you're looking to enhance your life beyond the screen, this video is for you. Watch now and discover how lessening time on social media made me richer in life.

snippet.description:
You won't believe what we found at The Manor! Bridgerton Georgian Dresses, Coronation Robes and an Invitation from The Queen! Like our Baseball caps?  Check out our brand new Mapperton Shop here: https://www.mapperton.online and get 10% OFF everything using the Promo Code: EARLYBIRD 
From beanies to hoodies to iPhone cases - over 30 Mapperton branded products!

🏡 Welcome to Mapperton, Englands' Finest Manor House!  Join us, Luke and Julie, for an enchanting 5-night retreat hosted by us at one of England's majestic estates. Experience the perfect blend of history and luxury. Discover more on our website: Grand Historic Tours: https://www.grandhistorictours.com

🌟 Join our Community! Thank you for being an integral part of our journey. Enhance your experience by becoming a member of our exclusive Patron community. Enjoy perks like behind-the-scenes content, live Q&As, and special gifts, all while supporting the preservation of our cherished historic estate. Join here: https://patreon.com/mappertonlive

The Gilded Age American Heiress Exhibition opened to the public here at Mapperton on the 5th May. However,  if you can’t make it in person you can buy a ticket (3 cups of coffee) for a virtual hour long tour with me, and support this ongoing project over at https://www.buymeacoffee.com/juliejmontagu

A new exhibition offers a glimpse into the captivating world of Alberta Sturges Montagu, the 9th Countess of Sandwich, and an American Heiress from the renowned era known as The Gilded Age. 

Curated by Mapperton’s very own American Viscountess, Julie Montagu, the "American Heiress" collection is comprised of more than 10,000 previously unseen letters exchanged between Alberta (Sturges) Montagu and her family, as well as the peerage at large. 

Dating from 1888 to 1951, these letters constitute the largest unpublished private collection of correspondence from the period. They offer a remarkable glimpse into the life of a "dollar bride" during the Gilded Age, shedding light on both triumphs and struggles.
 
The exhibition takes innovation to the next level by introducing Alberta AI, a ground-breaking creation that brings her story to life like never before. 

“With the aid of cutting-edge AI technology, we've resurrected Alberta's voice, allowing her to answer visitors’ burning questions about her remarkable journey,” says Julie Montagu, Viscountess Hinchingbrooke.

🏛️ Can't come visit us in person! No problem! How about a Virtual Tour of Mapperton House & Gardens! Explore the beauty of the English countryside through stunning 360-degree imagery, videos, and ambient sounds in our immersive virtual tour. Start your tour at: https://buymeacoffee.com/mapperton

🌍 Explore More with Us! Visit our sister channel: American Viscountess on YouTube (https://youtube.com/americanviscountess) and Julie's NEW channel:  Julie in Italy, Authentic Italy Delivered to your Doorstep on YouTube (https://youtube.com/julieinitaly) 

📚  Discover Julie's Best-Selling Books!  Did you know Julie is a best-selling author on health and wellbeing? Check out her good for you recipe books and more:

- Superfoods Superfast, 100 Energising Recipes to Make in 20 Minutes or Less: https://www.amazon.com/Superfoods-Superfast-Energizing-Recipes-Minutes/dp/1849497869

- Superfoods, The Flexible Approach to Eating More Superfood: https://www.amazon.com/Superfoods-Flexible-Approach-Eating-More/dp/1849496668

- Eat Real Foods, Simple Rules for Health Happiness and Unstoppable Energy https://www.amazon.com/Eat-Real-Food-Happiness-Unstoppable-ebook/dp/B017DOB1EO

- Recharge: A Year of Self-Care to Focus on You https://www.amazon.com/Recharge-Year-Self-Care-Focus-You/dp/0349418144

📬 Stay Informed! Subscribe to our monthly newsletter for the latest updates and events at Mapperton. Sign up here: https://mailchi.mp/mapperton/mapperton-mail

📅 Visit and Contribute to Mapperton!  Book your ticket now at https://mapperton.com to explore our Historic House, Award-wnning Gardens and Mapperton Wildlands, England's Most Spectacular Rewilding Project plus our new Gilded Age American Heiress exhibition. Contribute to our exhibition and archive materials at: https://www.buymeacoffee.com/juliejmontagu - A contribution of three cups of coffee or more grants you a virtual tour of the exhibition, led by Julie. 

We look forward to welcoming you to Mapperton soon! 🤗

Warm regards,  
Luke & Julie  
Viscount and Viscountess Hinchingbrooke 👑👑

snippet.title: Our Manor is Falling Down - and that’s just the beginning!
snippet.description:
🏡 Welcome to Mapperton, Englands' Finest Manor House!  Join us, Luke and Julie, for an enchanting 5-night retreat hosted by us at one of England's majestic estates. Experience the perfect blend of history and luxury. Discover more on our website: Grand Historic Tours: https://www.grandhistorictours.com

🌟 Join our Community! Thank you for being an integral part of our journey. Enhance your experience by becoming a member of our exclusive Patron community. Enjoy perks like behind-the-scenes content, live Q&As, and special gifts, all while supporting the preservation of our cherished historic estate. Join here: https://patreon.com/mappertonlive

The Gilded Age American Heiress Exhibition opened to the public here at Mapperton on the 5th May. However,  if you can’t make it in person you can buy a ticket (3 cups of coffee) for a virtual hour long tour with me, and support this ongoing project over at https://www.buymeacoffee.com/juliejmontagu

ROUND-BREAKING AI BRINGS HISTORY TO LIFE – NEW EXHIBITION UNVEILS THE UNTOLD STORY OF A GILDED AGE AMERICAN HEIRESS.  
 
A new exhibition offers a glimpse into the captivating world of Alberta Sturges Montagu, the 9th Countess of Sandwich, and an American Heiress from the renowned era known as The Gilded Age. 

Curated by Mapperton’s very own American Viscountess, Julie Montagu, the "American Heiress" collection is comprised of more than 10,000 previously unseen letters exchanged between Alberta (Sturges) Montagu and her family, as well as the peerage at large. 

Dating from 1888 to 1951, these letters constitute the largest unpublished private collection of correspondence from the period. They offer a remarkable glimpse into the life of a "dollar bride" during the Gilded Age, shedding light on both triumphs and struggles.
 
The exhibition will explore Alberta's formative years in America, her upbringing in Chicago and New York, and the significance of her inheritance. Visitors will unravel the captivating courtship between Alberta and George Montagu, the future 9th Earl of Sandwich, leading to their marriage in 1905 in London. The narrative will culminate with her relocation to Hinchingbrooke House, the original family seat, in 1916 as the new Countess, following the death of the 8th Earl of Sandwich.

The exhibition takes innovation to the next level by introducing Alberta AI, a ground-breaking creation that brings her story to life like never before. 

“With the aid of cutting-edge AI technology, we've resurrected Alberta's voice, allowing her to answer visitors’ burning questions about her remarkable journey,” says Julie Montagu, Viscountess Hinchingbrooke.

🏛️ Can't come visit us in person! No problem! How about a Virtual Tour of Mapperton House & Gardens! Explore the beauty of the English countryside through stunning 360-degree imagery, videos, and ambient sounds in our immersive virtual tour. Start your tour at: https://buymeacoffee.com/mapperton

Help support the restoration of our 18th-century Grade II* listed eagles at (https://www.gofundme.com/mappertoneagles). 

Shop for the latest Gilded Age American Heiress merchandise at the American Viscountess Shop https://www.americanviscountess.com/shop

- Superfoods Superfast, 100 Energising Recipes to Make in 20 Minutes or Less: https://www.amazon.com/Superfoods-Superfast-Energizing-Recipes-Minutes/dp/1849497869

- Superfoods, The Flexible Approach to Eating More Superfood: https://www.amazon.com/Superfoods-Flexible-Approach-Eating-More/dp/1849496668

snippet.title: HOUSE TOUR | Inside A Traditional Colonial Home in Oxford, Mississippi
snippet.description:
We’re bringing you to Oxford, Mississippi for a look inside interior designer Priscilla Wright’s darling home.

For more extraordinary home tours, visit our website: homeworthy.com

Fondly regarded as the Tree House, Priscilla’s colonial-style home is enveloped by gorgeous historic trees that line the property. Inspired by her surroundings, Priscilla has beautifully woven greens and leaf patterns into her classic and traditional decor. Enjoy!

Join the Guest House: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC2oAso3hNDqYxgqEEP-Esrw/join
 
Guest House Access - Playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=UUMO2oAso3hNDqYxgqEEP-Esrw

snippet.title: HOUSE TOUR | An Idyllic Wine Country Home
snippet.description:
Interior designer Lisa Furtado tours us through her home and gardens in the stunning Sonoma Wine Country region of California. 

For more extraordinary home tours, visit our website: homeworthy.com

The bright and lush landscape surrounding Lisa's historic home provided the perfect backdrop for the interiors – which she infused with a soothing and layered color palette that feels right out of a Nancy Meyers movie.

Her backyard – complete with a state-of-the-art outdoor kitchen, pool, dining area, and firepit – is the crown jewel of the space. With multiple bedrooms and entertaining spaces throughout the property, she has ensured her home is perfect for the many visitors that come through.

snippet.title: HOUSE TOUR | Inside the Collected Maryland Home of House and Garden Dog
snippet.description:
On today's episode of Homeworthy, we're on the Eastern Shore of Maryland, visiting Phaedra Brown – she is known for posting beautiful photos of her home on her Instagram account, House and Garden Dog. 

Phaedra describes her style as layered, colorful and traditional all with an english influence. 

She loves the  feeling of English country homes, with their bold and sometimes unexpected blending of colors and patterns. Adding to the charm of her interiors is Phaedra’s adorable West Highland Terrier, Wellie. Enjoy!

snippet.title: VLOG #8: A day in my life
snippet.description:
24 hours in my life: From going to my hairdresser in Liverpool, taking blog photos in Tarporley and the Abbeywood Estate wearing my new Boden dress to buying some new plants. Just pretty normal stuff.

Here's the blog post to my skin routine: http://thelifbissue.com/en/skin-care-routine-for-mature-skin/ (English version)

snippet.title: Married Life - Are we weird? #marriedlife #couplelife
snippet.description:
Married Life - Are we weird?// Hello! I wanted to make a different kind of vlog - a very unpolished and raw vlog of Joerg and me. It's just us living our life and yes, we've been together for 30 years at the end of this month. Joerg isn't only my husband, he's my partner in crime and my best friend. Our life has always been adventurous, weird at times but we wouldn't want it any other way. And your feedback on this one would mean so much to me/us. Would you like to see more of these vlogs? A mixture of both polished and then very real vlogs? Your comments are highly appreciated.x

_____

RECIPE GLUTEN FREE SAUSAGE ROLLS:

Ingredients:

 2 large chicken breasts, 3 rashers streaky bacon, thinly sliced, 4 sundried tomatoes - chopped, handful basil leaves – chopped,  gluten free puff pastry, gluten free flour for dusting, 1 egg yolk, sesame seeds

Method:

1. Whizz the chicken and garlic in a processor until the chicken is minced. Tip in the bacon, sundried tomatoes and basil. Pulse for 5 secs to just mix through. Season well.

2. Roll the pastry sheet on a lightly floured surface and cut in half lengthways. Spread half the chicken mixture along the middle of one of the pastry strips, then roll up the pastry, pinching the ends together to seal. 

3. Heat oven to 220C/180C fan/gas6. Place the rolls on a large baking sheet. Brush with the egg, then sprinkle with seeds. Bake for 20 mins until golden. Cut into 2.5 m long pieces.

_____

RECIPE GLUTEN FREE EGG & CRESS CLUB SANDWICH:

Ingredients:

 2 eggs, 2 tbsp mayonnaise, gluten free bread, butter, cress, 2-3 slices of tomato or lettuce leaf and a slice of ham or cheese

Method:

1. Bring a pan of water to the boil and carefully lower in the eggs. Cook for 6 mins, then cool under running water until they can be peeled. Peel the eggs, then leave to cool completely.

2. Mash or chop the eggs, then mix with mayonnaise and some seasoning if you like. Toast the bread.

3. Lay one slice of bread on a board. Butter it, then spread on three quarters of the egg and scatter over the cress. Add another slice of toast and gently spread on the remaining mayo. Add the tomato or lettuce and ham or cheese (or whichever combination you prefer).  Top with the final piece of toast. Cut the crusts off if you like, then gently cut the sandwich into four quarters, being careful not to squash out the egg.

_____

snippet.description:
OUR ATTIC ROOM RENOVATION: WE MADE A MISTAKE!// Hello, Today we are sharing the dilemma of our attic room. I actually made a very big mistake and because of that it made us realise that Joerg and I didn't listen to what our gut feeling was telling us from the very beginning. snippet.title: How We Brought our GILDED AGE Countess of Sandwich Back to Life!  - It’s Unbelievable!
snippet.description:
How we brought our Gilded Age American Heiress 'back to life' using AI is truly remarkable! 
Visit https://foreo.se/5l3f for 30% off UFO 3 plus an additional 10% discount for the first 50 that use the coupon code : MAPPERTON10

The Gilded Age American Heiress Exhibition opened to the public here at Mapperton on the 5th May. However,  if you can’t make it in person you can buy a ticket (3 cups of coffee) for a virtual hour long tour with me, and support this ongoing project over at https://www.buymeacoffee.com/juliejmontagu

ROUND-BREAKING AI BRINGS HISTORY TO LIFE – NEW EXHIBITION UNVEILS THE UNTOLD STORY OF A GILDED AGE AMERICAN HEIRESS.  
 
A new exhibition offers a glimpse into the captivating world of Alberta Sturges Montagu, the 9th Countess of Sandwich, and an American Heiress from the renowned era known as The Gilded Age. 

Curated by Mapperton’s very own American Viscountess, Julie Montagu, the "American Heiress" collection is comprised of more than 10,000 previously unseen letters exchanged between Alberta (Sturges) Montagu and her family, as well as the peerage at large. 

Dating from 1888 to 1951, these letters constitute the largest unpublished private collection of correspondence from the period. They offer a remarkable glimpse into the life of a "dollar bride" during the Gilded Age, shedding light on both triumphs and struggles.
 
The exhibition will explore Alberta's formative years in America, her upbringing in Chicago and New York, and the significance of her inheritance. Visitors will unravel the captivating courtship between Alberta and George Montagu, the future 9th Earl of Sandwich, leading to their marriage in 1905 in London. The narrative will culminate with her relocation to Hinchingbrooke House, the original family seat, in 1916 as the new Countess, following the death of the 8th Earl of Sandwich.

The exhibition takes innovation to the next level by introducing Alberta AI, a ground-breaking creation that brings her story to life like never before. 

“With the aid of cutting-edge AI technology, we've resurrected Alberta's voice, allowing her to answer visitors’ burning questions about her remarkable journey,” says Julie Montagu, Viscountess Hinchingbrooke.

Shop for the latest Gilded Age American Heiress merchandise at the American Viscountess Shop https://www.americanviscountess.com/shop

snippet.title: HOUSE TOUR | Inside a Transitional Home in Charlotte
snippet.description:
On today's episode of Homeworthy, we're in Charlotte, NC, visiting the home of interior designer Alexis Pawling. Alexis lives with her family in a gorgeous home with transitional touches and bright pops of color. Born and raised on the Upper East Side of Manhattan, Alexis developed a love for beautiful architecture and design from a young age. Her aesthetic is founded on classic design principles, blending color, texture, and pattern to create smart and energetic living spaces. Enjoy!

snippet.title: 🏰 Buckingham Palace - The FULL Tour of King Charles III Royal Residence (Coronation) London Guide 🏰
snippet.description:
This is a full guided tour around Buckingham Palace: the most famous Royal Palace in the world! Located in Central London near Westminster Abbey and Big Ben, it’s home to King Charles III, formerly Queen Elizabeth II and the Royal Family. But can you go inside, and where do you buy tickets? The answer is yes, I’ll help you out with all of that. Unlike most of the fraudulent videos out there on YouTube, this is the Buckingham Palace video you’ve been looking for.

I’ll show you around everything including the Grand Entrance, Grand Staircase, Throne Room, Green Drawing Room, Blue Drawing Room, White Drawing Room, Picture Gallery, State Dining Room, Grand Ballroom, East Gallery, Music Room, 1844 Room, Marble Hall, the Bow Room, Minister’s Steps and more.

I’ll even show you around the Palace Gardens, the Royal Mews and the Queen’s Gallery, all in one handy video!

20:05 – Summary, Tips & Advice

snippet.title: Windsor Castle Tour - The Queen's Royal Residence - England Travel Ideas
snippet.description:
Windsor Castle is one of the most picturesque castles in England. It has over 900 years of history and is currently the Queen’s weekend Royal residence. She considers Buckingham Palace the ‘office’ and Windsor Castle her actual home. If you like the Royal Castles and history – Windsor Castle should be on top of your list! Ninh shows you exactly what it’s like to go around one of the best castles in the United Kingdom.

✝ RIP QUEEN ELIZABETH II - 21st April 1926 - 8th September 2022 ✝ 
You were the longest serving and best monarch this country ever had.
Thank you for your life of service to our great nation and commonwealth and may you rest in peace, forever in the adulation and gratitude of the British people.

snippet.title: Inside The State Rooms Of Windsor Castle With Dan Snow
snippet.description:
'Inside The State Rooms Of Windsor Castle With Dan Snow'

Windsor Castle has a legendary connection to the British monarchy: the longest-serving royal palace in the whole of Europe. 

Ever since the days of William the Conqueror, the castle has dominated this strategic point on the banks of the River Thames, overlooking west London. Over the next millennium kings and queens would invest lavish amounts in its development. 

As a result, today it is one of the most magnificent sites in the British Isles. In this video, curator Kate Heard provides Dan Snow with an exclusive tour of the castle's beautiful state rooms and interior.

snippet.title: Dan Snow Uncovers The Secrets Of Westminster Abbey
snippet.description:
Exploring The Incredible Royal Tombs Of Westminster Abbey 

In this video, historian Dan Snow joins Sir David Cannadine to explore the complex history of religious affiliation at Westminster Abbey, which has evolved from being a Catholic monastery to a Protestant cathedral, with monarchs buried at the site representing a range of beliefs. He also discusses the various tombs, statues, monuments, and effigies in the abbey, highlighting how the process of memorialization has changed over time, with physical burials now rare and reserved for the most notable figures. Cannadine also takes viewers on a tour of the tombs, noting the juxtaposition of Winston Churchill's tomb and the Unknown Warrior's monument, and discussing how modes of commemoration and celebration continue to evolve in the 21st century.

This episode was filmed before the death of Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II.

snippet.title: What Was Life Actually Like In Ancient Roman London? | Life and Death Roman London
snippet.description:
Join us on an immersive journey through the ancient streets of Roman London. We explore archaeological finds that offer glimpses into daily life, from deciphered wax tablets revealing trade dealings to artifacts like spearheads, arrowheads, and fragments of armor. London's Roman history traces back to around 50 AD, when a mercantile trading post was established on a gravel terrace above the river Thames. At the time, this area was a floodplain surrounded by thick woods. But this muddy valley would eventually become one of the greatest cities in the world.

snippet.title: What Was Life Really Like for Medieval Nobility in Europe?
snippet.description:
In the medieval feudal system, the nobility were generally those who held a fief, often land or office under vassalage in exchange for military allegiance to their sovereign. 

Living alongside serfs, it was their duty to ensure that the peasants, craftsmen and clergymen were defended so that they could live in peace and act as judges to handle disputes.

To explore the often ostentatious and gluttonous lifestyles of the nobility, Eleanor Janega visits Hedingham Castle, perhaps the best preserved Norman keep in Essex, England.

snippet.title: What Was Everyday Life Like In Medieval Britain?
snippet.description:
What Was Life Really Like For A Medieval Peasant? 

Watch the full episode of 'Going Medieval: Those Who Work' on History Hit TV: https://access.historyhit.com/going-medieval/videos/those-who-work

In the Medieval period, peasants made up roughly 80% of the European population. But what was life really like for a peasant during the Middle Ages? Under the feudal system, was it all backbreaking toil on the land, working for a local lord? What did it actually mean to be a peasant? And how did it differ from being a serf? 

In the first episode of Going Medieval, Dr Eleanor Janega visits Denny Abbey, a former Benedictine monastery in Cambridge to explore the lives of those who devoted their lives to working the land.

snippet.title: The Life of the Medieval ‘Middle Class’ in England
snippet.description:
What was life really like for the merchants, craftsmen and traders in London in the middle ages?

Whilst the majority of people who worked in the Medieval Period were peasants, a significant community of merchants and tradesmen existed, the majority of whom belonged to one of the most powerful and influential groups in medieval Europe - the Guilds. 

Guilds were associations of artisans and merchants who oversaw the practice of their craft or trade in a particular area. They were able to command prestige and power over medieval populations and membership of these organisations was extremely desirable. The Grocers' Guild for example, which oversaw the trade in spices (one of the most expensive and important commodities in the Middle Ages) was an incredibly rich and powerful association as is very apparent by the opulence and grandeur of Grocers' Hall in London. 

In this video, Dr Eleanor Janega visits the banqueting hall to explore the lives of those who earned in medieval London.

snippet.title: How Much Power Did the Catholic Church Have in the Middle Ages?
snippet.description:
One of the most unifying elements of the Medieval Period was the Roman Catholic Church. All classes and ranks of people, whether that be nobles, peasants or tradesmen, were profoundly affected by the rulings of the church. 

A hierachy existed within the clergy. Following the pope, in order of rank, there were bishops, priests, monks and nuns. In the latter part of the Middle Ages, the pope, as head of the church, had a huge influence over the monarchy and total control of the clergy.

In this video, medieval historian Dr Eleanor Janega explores the lives of those who made up the single largest unifying organization in medieval Europe.
